The DÃ­sir hold a revered place as powerful female ancestral spirits connected to family lines, which emphasizes a connection to one's ancestors and heritage, the DÃ­sir are seen as protectors and guides, deeply tied to the well-being and survival of the tribe. The disir are the female spirits. The Valkyries have been known as Odin's disir, the female landvettir , the land disir. The DÃ­sir are often thought to be the spirits of deceased female ancestors who continue to watch over their descendants, offering blessings, wisdom, and sometimes warnings. They are guardians of the family, ensuring prosperity, fertility, and the protection of the bloodline. The DÃ­sablÃ³t, a key ritual, was traditionally held to honor these spirits, asking for their favor in the coming year, especially during times of crisis or hardship. The bond between the living and their ancestors is sacred, with the DÃ­sir representing the continuity of heritage. This worldview stresses the importance of maintaining ancestral customs, values, and the honoring of family ties through ritual. The DÃ­sir embody the idea that the past informs the present, and by honoring them, we strengthen their connection to their roots and ensure the blessings of their foremothers continue to flow through future generations. DÃ­sirblÃ³t: A Ritual to Honor the Ancestral Spirits Items Needed: A small altar or sacred space A bowl of mead (or another drink offering) Fresh flowers or fruit as an offering A candle (preferably white) A small piece of food (such as bread or cake) Cleanse your space, call in the directions, smudge. Set the altar with the cloth, offerings, and candle. Ground yourself through deep breathing or a brief meditation, focusing on your ancestral connection. Light the candle and say: "Hail to the DÃ­sir, mighty protectors of my line, Ancestors, wise and strong, who walk with me through time. I call upon you this night, with gratitude and heart, Guide and guard me, never to part. Pour the mead into the offering bowl, lifting it to the sky. Say: "To the DÃ­sir, I offer this gift of mead. May your blessings flow through me and my kin. Accept this humble offering as a sign of my respect and love." Place the flowers or fruit on the altar and say: "As these flowers (or fruit) are full of life, so too may our family be vibrant and protected by your grace." Take a moment to reflect on your ancestors or offer a personal prayer, speaking from the heart. You may wish to mention specific female ancestors or simply honor the collective DÃ­sir. Take a small sip of the mead (if appropriate) and leave the rest for the DÃ­sir, either outside under a tree or in a natural space after the ritual. Extinguish the candle, saying: "Hail the DÃ­sir, who watch over me. May you always guide my steps. Until we meet again." By Harvala, Heather Clinkenbeard Try Folk, Raven Folk United! Faith, Family, Folk The triad of Faith, Family, and Folk forms the foundation of a meaningful and balanced life, reflecting values rooted deeply in ancient Norse tradition. Each principle is essential and interconnected, yet the order, faith, family, and folk. holds significance. Faith, which serves as the spiritual compass guiding an individual's life. Faith in the gods, the sacredness of nature, and the wisdom of the ancestors strengthens oneâ€™s connection to the divine and the cosmos. This faith offers both purpose and direction, forming the bedrock upon which all other values rest. It is through faith that we align ourselves with the teachings of the gods, such as Odin's pursuit of wisdom and Thorâ€™s protection of Midgard. After faith comes family, for the family unit is the core of one's personal life and lineage. Family is not only biological but also extends to those bonded by shared values and culture. Family is where teachings of the ancestors are passed down, where loyalty is nurtured, and where strength is drawn in times of hardship. A strong family upholds the values of the folk and ensures the survival of tradition through the generations. The third pillar, folk, represents the broader community or tribe that one belongs to. In ancient Norse culture, kinship and tribal loyalty were crucial for survival and identity. Raven folk belief reflects this, emphasizing solidarity with one's folk, those who share your ancestry, culture, and traditions. The well-being of the folk ensures the preservation of the communityâ€™s culture, language, and spiritual practices. The order of these principles reflects a hierarchy of values especially for Raven Folk. Faith comes first because it is the source of spiritual grounding, guiding both personal and communal actions. Family follows, as the immediate circle of support and responsibility. Finally, folk stands as the extension of oneâ€™s family and culture, embodying the larger community that sustains the individual and the family alike. By living according to these principles, faith first, followed by family, then folk, an We honor the Gods, strengthens their kin, and preserve our people. Redbad King of Frisians Along the coast of Western Europe, where some of its major rivers meet the salt water of the North Sea, there has lived a Germanic tribe of people called the Frisians. They made their presence known to the invading Romans as far back as 12 BC and were noted, at that time, as one of the warring factions resisting foreign occupation. As Rome increased their subjugation, Frisians rose against all odds and defeated the regional Roman Governor. This defeat won them greater freedom for some time. During the seventh and eighth centuries, after Rome had become Christianized, the western region of the Holy Roman Empire, the Franks, had pushed this religion up into Frisia, building Christian churches in major Frisian towns. The leader at the time, Aldgisl, had defeated the Franks in several battles and had bountiful harvest. It seemed they were in acting in good favor with this new god and did not fear the threat of Christian practices. Once he died, his heir Redbad destroyed the Christian churches There is a legend from this time that the foreign leader of occupying Frankish forces, King Charles, asked for the 12 wisest Frisian men to be brought before him to give him the laws in which they lived. Having been suited to settling disputes amongst smaller groups, therefore having a variety of ways to find peace, they had no clear overriding set of rules in which to govern. This was not acceptable to the foreign leader and he gave them the choice to be enslaved, put to death or set afloat on the sea in a rudderless boat. They chose the boat. Having no rudder, the tide took them far out to sea and after a couple of days, their fate seemed to be set. They prayed to the Gods for salvation and in particular Forseti, bringer of law and order. A mist fell about the ship and when it cleared, there was a thirteenth passenger, who carried a great gleaming ax, heavily inlaid with gold. They had never seen the likeness of such a splendid weapon. The stranger took the ax, plunged it into the water and used it as a steering oar to guide the ship to an island off shore of Frisia. Once ashore the stranger took his golden ax and hurled it to the ground and released a stream of water that quenched the dying thirst of the twelve men. Then the stranger recited a comprehensive set of laws that all Frisians could live by. From then on that island became a sacred island in honor of the God Forseti. This island is now callled Heligoland and used to be called Heyligeland, or 'holy land', possibly due to the island's long association with the God Forseti. The men returned to deliver the laws for which King Charles had asked. These laws are still known as Lex Frisionum. By RFU Regional Jarl, Shea McCurdy

Hail the Folk Heroes! Redbad-King of the Frisians Redbad came into power after the death of his long lived predecessor, Aldgisl. Aldgisl had fought against the Franks during his reign and had been successful. He had even given asylum to a Christian monk that fled England and was also no friend of the Franks. Some of Aldgislâ€™s royal court had even converted, but the Old Whip, as Aldgislâ€™s name is translated, did not. After the Old Whip likely died of natural causes at age 74 in the year 680, Redbad, who may have been his son, but at least from an elite Frisian family, was crowned. Like Aldgisl, Redbad fought many battles against the Franks, but with much less success. This led to his defeat by Pepin in 695 at Dorestad. The Franks then claimed territory up to the Rhine River. Redbad and Pepin made peace through a union of Redbadâ€™s daughter, and Pepinâ€™s eldest son. This peace lasted almost twenty years until Pepinâ€™s death in 714, wherein there was some chaos amongst the Franks. Redbad took advantage of this and successfully won back Frisian lands and cities. Redbad handed heir and another son of Pepin, Charles Martel, known for his crusades, Martelâ€™s only defeat at Cologne. Redbad banned Christianity and destroyed Christian churches while raising an army with the intent of invading Frankish lands. Before he led that invasion, he died in 719 on the island later to be called Heligoland or holy land known for being a sacred island upon which the God Forseti is honored. Redbadâ€™s memory still haunted the Franks as they rumored he was asleep with his army in a mountain, where ravens circled. The story says that when the ravens stopped circling, he would awaken and exact vengeance on the Franks. Redbad is known for his false baptism. He had one foot in the baptismal font and paused to ask if he would meet his ancestors in the heaven the Christians had preached about so often. The monk Wolfram is said to have replied that since they had not converted that they would spend all eternity burning in Hell. Speaking of Redbadâ€™s noble ancestors as if they were nothing more than common thieves enraged Redbad and he warned Wolfram to leave and stay out of his sight on Earth, in Heaven or in Hell. Staying true to his Gods and Ancestors while fighting for his Folkâ€™s independence, King Redbad has earned our respect and a place as an RFU honored hero and celebrate his deeds during the Blood month. Honor him with your loved ones, share his stories and commitment to his Gods and Ancestors. Show us your celebrations so we can build upon such legendary memories. There are a plethora of articles to site that tell the tales of Redbad, and even a feature length movie, â€œRedbadâ€. Another tale for another time about Forsetiâ€™s connection to Frisia is worth a gander, too. All in all, the Frisians have a unique culture amongst the Germanic peoples and a rich history of standing up for themselves and their past. Hail the doers! Hail the Frisians! Hail King Redbad! By RFU Regional Jarl, Shea McCurdy

DAY OF REMEMBRANCE FOR KING RADBOD OF FRISIA This month we celebrate valiant King Radbod of Frisia. King of Frisia from about 680 CE onwards he was responsible for keeping his lands free of Frankish domination and is often described as Frisiaâ€™s last independent ruler. Radbod spent the bulk of his reign battling against the neighboring Franks, first fighting against Pippin II until he died in 714 and then against Pippinâ€™s son, Charles Martel. Radbod also did all he could to push Christianity out of his lands, in christianity he saw an extension of Frankish influence and control; he also saw it as a destroyer of his own native Frisian culture. The battles between Radbod and the Franks went back and forth until finally in 714, with the death of Pippin, Radbod was able to send all the priests and monks out of his lands and pushed the Frankish armies completely out as well until his death in 719. Radbod is perhaps best known to Odinists today for his refusal to be baptized in the Christian faith. Radbod was on the verge of being baptized when he turned to the priest and asked if he would see his ancestors in heaven. The priest, being honest(for once), said no, anyone not of the Christian faith was sent to suffer in their horrid fiery realm of punishment which they called Hell. Radbod replied, â€ Then I would rather be suffering there with them than go to heaven with a pack of beggars.â€ He then promptly pushed the priests out of his country and remained tru to his ancestral ways until his death. Radbod has much to teach us today. We arenâ€™t forced at sword point to accept alien religions today, but we do find ourselves in a similar position. For many today the forward march of political correctness has led right to our doorsteps. We have become pariahs in the eyes of society because we refuse to accept its decadent ways and yet here we are. Here we are remaining steadfast in our loyalty and devotion to our Gods. We have shunned the foreign influences of our age and sent them scurrying from our homes. Rather than slide into the negative mindset of a beaten opponent we hold our heads high and boldly build positivity in ourselves, in our families, and in all those we can around us. We are assured of the rightness of our deeds by the echoes from the past of brave men like Radbod. Hail noble King Radbod of Frisia! By Gothi Blaine Qualls

From the Aesirian code of 9 Honor: Honor oneself with truth and fairness. Your word is your bond. Give power to your word by adhering to it. Honor your family and friends with reverence and respect. Honor your love and the way above all else. Honor is the mark of strength and nobility. I copied this from Gothi Zach Catos book, The Northern Way. It comes up for me as I witness our folk and the issues they have with their partners. So often we get caught is this negative pull in the relationship that we have a hard time seeing things clearly. We get stuck on the small things and take each other for granted. It's really important to escape that pull and stand outside the relationship from time to time and see what needs to be healed. Mostly I see people get used to each other and stop treating them like the partner they are. Especially if you have children. Understand times can be hard, each of you can be going through something. When you are, be honest and when someone speaks up, listen with compassion and allow each other space. Offer help and suggestions. Be there for each other. One of the most important things in a relationship is to make your partner feel supported. Ask yourself, do you? Check your own actions and think, if you were your partner would you be happy? We are all in this moment together, in historical saga times, for a reason. The Norns have called the few together to seize the future of our Folk. As we embark on this great new idea of a Folk Nation, we must remember our past but not live in it. Honoring our ancestors and traditions must never be confused with fantasy. What was then is now gone and we are all that is left. Our time is now and the future is full of glory unbound, if only we are bold enough to seize it! Time has come to pick up the torch and move forward toward our wyrd! We must as individuals, independently from one another with due diligence, make a disciplined and consistent effort towards nobility and spiritual growth. It is not only our birthright but our duty, as individuals, to continuously develop so that collectively we can manifest and execute real changes in the real world today. No longer is the luxury of procrastination or constant self-indulgence an option! Those unwilling or unable to make these realizations are directly, even if unconsciously, contributing to the downfall of our Folk! As in all times we mortal men and women are faced with a unique challenge. A monumental task is before us. An underlying duty has risen in which each of us must make the choice. I look at all of you amongst us, asking with a great urgency yet fully confident in our path toâ€¦ Rise up, kinsman! From today forth, hold this Nation as it is, your tribal people and Folk Nation! What is the point of being a member of the Raven Folk United Nation? Membership means we have background checked those that are members and ran their names through the federal Sex offender registry. It is a safety measure for our Folk. To know that when you interact with each other that you know we have to the best of our abilities, checked to make sure they do not pose a threat to you, your child or your spouse. And that we will recheck our members again once a year after that to ensure that if something is on the registry, that we will find it. We have a ZERO tolerance policy. If that person is on the registry we do NOT entertain the possibility of membership. It is denied. Or if found later during a re check, it is revoked. Our people our hardwired for Tribe. We are meant to live in communities and be a help to each other. Your family comes 1st, then your Kindred, then your wider community. We do not dictate spiritual practices at RFU. If you honor the Aesir, and you value the preservation of your Northern ways and people, that is who we are. We encourage and support you individually and as a Kindred. The stronger the individual, the stronger the kindred/tribes. Then so to the stronger the Nation. I believe there will come a time when knowing we are all out there, Bonded by the blood of our shared ancestry, the living decendents of those mighty, mighty Gods. And United in purpose, will be important to the continued growth and survival of our people. Coming together to say "My Tribe will stand with yours. That we will hold the line when the time comes to defend our people, and our Folk ways", is vital. Raven Folk United is the means to building bonds accross midgard. Our ancestors took care of their own but they knew the benefit to alliances and bonds. It is how they flourished, prospered and grew in times of old. We must reclaim that ability to unite as a nation. To reclaim the pride of our people. To share our knowledge. Our tribes can not stay disconnected and our people thrive. Those two things can not happen simultaneously. Now is the time to heal old wounds. To shake hands with your neighboring tribes. To find that common ground. Plant our flags in that ground. And to rise as one nation! United in purpose! I urge you to look at Raven Folk United anew. I will share the link here. Read about us. What we wish to build together with you. And if it resonates, then band together with us. By Gythia Melissa Mills Ravenfolkunited.org

Let us smile and embrace the new day with all of its beauty and in the face of all struggles to come, united in purpose, we will push forward towards a future of community and true Frith amongst kinsman. Happy New Year to all of the Raven folk! Hail Raven Folk United! HAIL OUR MIGHTY GODS!!!! âš¡ravenfolkunited.org

A glad ending and spectacular new beginings to you on this, the 12th Day of Yule! This night is for all divine friends and Oaths! And today we think on wisdom! Leave offerings for your land spirits today to entice them to stay through the cold seasons and to bless your lands! Give offering to the house spirits, so that your home is filled with cheer, love, abundance and cleanliness! Focus tonight on what your goals are for the year and give blot to the God or Goddess that makes most sense, to exchange the best of what you have to offer in hopes that they will lend their aid and and blessings in return. If you are not sure which one, ask your Gothi/Gythia for guidance. Raven Folk United has some who are also quite happy to help if you do not have that spiritual guidance local to you yet. We are always happy to have spiritual conversations to help when needed. 12th night is also a time where our people jump the fire! Leaving in the past all that they do not wish to carry into the future. Letting it burn off over the fire! (Please use caution if you choose to do this, we dont want to see pics of ambulance rides because you burned off more than you bargained for..ğŸ˜³ğŸ˜œ) Another tradition is to oath over the boars head. You may see actual boars heads or wooden ones that people lay their hands on to make their oaths for the next year. This tradition has roots in the Boar, Gullinbursti(Golden Bristle) Freyrs golden bristled boar that shone like the light of a thousand suns! At such a time when we celebrate the return of the sun it easy to see why sow day was a part of Yule. Where the people would get together to slaughter and prepare the boar for the Yule feast. In days of old the best boar would be brought into the hall where everyone would lay a hand upon it, swearing oaths that would be heard by Freyr! Then they would slaughter the boar in offering and feast! Another to hear your oaths is Var(pledge or beloved). She is the Goddess of oaths, agreements and contracts. She hears the oaths, even the private ones, between men and women. So if you are looking to give blot before an Oath tonight, this may be your girl. On the subject of oaths: remeber that an oath is reciprocal. That means there is a give and take, an exchange. And if you are oathing amongs your folk know that they become a part of that oath. That they are bound to help you achieve that oaths completion. And should you fail, you effect the wyrd of all. So do not take an oath lightly. It is why an oath must be discussed before taking it and those who will be present need to make the choice to be there or step out for it. Think tonight on wisdom as well. Odin says it is best to be middling wise. Knowing to much may bring sorrow. And not enough may lead to ill choices. But knowing a middling amount, that is the sweet spot. Knowing enough to still learn. To still be in awe of the mysteries of our world and the one beyond the veil. Knowing enough to use what knowledge you have to make good decisions for yourself, your family, your community. That is wisdom in practice. As we get ready to bid the 12 holy days that reside neither in the last year or in the one about to start, these 12 holy days suspended in the middle, my heart is full. My wishes are clear. And my gratitude for all the blessings I have recieved in this life is overflowing. So light your 12th candle. Speak your oaths. Share your prosperity in goods or goodwill and love. Embrace your family, your kith and kin one more time in the in between. Then jump over the fire! Leave the past where it may lay, and take on the future! Hail the Divine Friends! Hail to those who take on serious Oaths! And Hail to wisdom this night! I will see you all next year! Many blessings!â¤ï¸ Gythia Melisa Mills âš¡ravenfolkunited.org

Wishing you a glorious 11th Night of Yule! Today belongs to the Valkyries and the warriors! In Old Norse: valkyrja, means 'chooser of the slain' The Valkeries are sometimes said to be mortals given a task of choosing the slain who will then abide in Vallhal with Ã“Ã°in to fight at Ragnorok. In some writings they are considered the daughters of Ã“Ã°in. And some say that they are half mortal and half divine. Brunhildr was the a Valkyrie and daughter of King Budli, Sigrun was also a Valkyrie and was daughter to King Hogni. So it is possible that they were in part, mortal. They are written of also, as being like their own army and participating in battles. And in Njals Saga they write of 12 Valkeries seen in a stone hut weaving, and deciding who of the slain shall abide in Valhall. One of the Valkyries is named Skuld, like the Norn. And so I wonder if the mortal women, or half mortal women, and the Norn Skuld, could all have very well taken part in the choosing of the slain. But whatever the truth may be, the service, the task they performed was important. As the warriors would feast, fight, die and start anew each day in Valhall in preparation for the ultimate battle, Ragnorok. Choosing the best warriors would be very important. The heavens and Midgard would depend on it. And those warriors; those who left it all on the field of combat. Chosen for their might, honor, bravery and perhaps some for the berserker nature. It is they that will stand with the Gods at Ragnorok. It is they that will once again ride into battle ready to sacrifice it all! In the name of their Gods, and their people! Today we also honor the virtue of self reliance. Strive to be self sufficient. To be one others can rely upon to carry the weight of those tasks they take on. To be a help and not a hinderance within your family and community! Hail the Valkyries! Hail the noble Warriors! Hail those who are self reliant! By Gythia Melisa Mills âš¡ravenfolkunited.org

Wishing you a blessed 9th night of Yule! Today is sacred to Odin, yes, he gets a second feast night! Today we honor him as not the lord of the wild hunt, but in his role as father. As tonight we also honor the Alfar, our male ancestors. Where would we be without them? The many battles fought to protect their families and their people. The strong backs and calused hands that have labored to build that which you have inherited. Inheritance is not just worldy goods, no, it is much more than that. Thousands came before you. Your blood still sings their song. Your heart still beats with the same rythm. Without even one of them, you would not be here. Your children would not be here. Odin sacrificed himself, and his eye that he would gain the wisdom needed to be a strong king in Asguard. To protect his people and to prepare for their future. Our Alfar also sacrificed through wars, famines, depressions, and plagues to make sure that the line of their people would continue. Tonight set a place for the fathers. Prepare a favorite meal of one of your Alfar, and honor the beloved dead. Tell their stories and let them live again at the feast table. Raise a glass to their names and deeds! Alongside them honor Odin and his sacrifices that allow for us to be here today. He did not fade into obscurity. He has stayed with our people through the thousand years our people were misguded and coerced into the shackles of a foreign God. He has called us home. Called for us to break those shakles and take back what is our birthright! He has embraced us with the tough love of a father. His way has not been to cajole but to shake the heavens and roar that our people are one! That our place is side by side. And the future of our children depends on the strength of our people today. What will you leave them? What would you sacrifice to give them a worthy and long lasting inheritance? It is also fitting that todays virtue is honor. It is ones reputation among the folk. It is also a personal code that beats inside the chest of good men and women. It is the combination of earned respect, honesty and pride. Honor or a lack of it, will dictate how you are seen in this lifetime. And it will shape the stories told at the table long after you are gone from this world. A lack of it will see your name spoken in scorn or shame, if you even merit being mentioned at all. But a life of honorable deeds will see you kept alive on the tongues of your decendents. And you may continue then to shape and inspire those that come after you. Strive to live with honor. Be the example your children and your community needs. And in so doing bring pride and gratitude from your Disir and Alfar, that you have not wasted that which they sacrificed to give you. And claim your place among those who never truly die. Hail the the Beloved Dead! Hail the Honor bound! Hail the Alfar! Hail Odin! By Gythia Melisa Mills âš¡ravenfolkunited.org

Wishing you a a Glad 8th night of Yule! Today we honor 2 of our Gods: Skaddi, and Ullr Skaddi was a giantess who loved Baldr but married Njordr in an ill fated match that ended when Njord could no longer stand to abide in the cold and snow of her home, and she could not live in the light and warmth of Njordrs home by the sea. She is Goddess of the winter. Ullr is also a God of the winter. Both are associated with the mountains, winter and hunting. And it is them we would ask for safe passage in the snows of winter, the hunt to sustain us with food for the winter months. So set them a place at your table tonight and thank them for your continued safe passage through the winter. And a blessed hunt if you are a huntsman or huntress. Today we also think on the virtue of Truth. To live in untruth is a shadowy existence. To fabricate falsehoods leads others to distrust and question you. But to speak truth brings honor and trust. It is not always easy to speak the truth. Sometimes you find that you stand alone. And have to watch as others falter when the the truth would force them to act in a way that would seperate them from the herd. Speak the truth anyway. You have to be the one to sleep at night with the choices you make. Make the choices that honor the virtue of truth. You will respect yourself far more. And your own opinion of yourself is worth far more than that of society. Hail Skaddi! Hail Ullr! And hail the truth Seekers and Speakers! By Gythia Melisa Mills Hail Raven Folk United! HAIL OUR MIGHTY GODS!! âš¡ravenfolkunited.org

Glad 7th Night of Yule! Tonight we Honor Thor! Children! And Fidelity! Thor has his place solidily held in the Yuletide celebration of our Ancestors! Our ancestors gave sacrifice and held feasts at this Yule festival time all for fertility, livestock, crops and, humans! Thor, as the protector of man holds his place in the death and rebirth aspect of the Yule celebrations. It is he who beats back the darkness as it tries to encroach upon Sol while she strives to bring forth the light of the sun. He is also the defender and protector of the common man, like our farmers. And he can bring the rain that waters the crops in the fields. So while Thor isnt seen as one of the most prominent of fertility Gods he has a solid assisting role in the growth of crops, livestock and humans. We see his influence still so strongly today in our Yuletide traditions. Fashioned from the last harvested sheaf of wheat is the Yule goat. A symbol of Thor. Burned to honor him and in the hopes of his continued protection of them and the continued growth and fertility of their crops and livestock. The tradition of caroling came from Wassailing and it was tradition to don the mask of a goat while wassailing. House to house they wld go, garnering hospitality and gifts of food. It is possible these were meant as offerings to Thor himself. Wassailing was often taken out to the orchards and they would sing through the trees. It is perhaps due to Thor that we burn the Yule log. As his close tie to Oak may have played a part. It would not be a stretch to assosiate the 2. A fun fact, Thors Goats, teethgrinder and teethnasher can be seen as thunder and lightning. Donnor and Blitzen=Thunder and Lightning. Is it possible they were the inspiration for 2 of santas reindeer, I think its plausable. ğŸ˜Š So honor Thor this night! By Yule goat! Singing to chase away the bad spirits as in wassailing! Lighting a candle to help chase the darkness away! And set a plate for him tonight. Share your harvest and abundance with him in appreciation of his protection and the rain. And dont forget a goodly portion of mead for the red haired, thunder God! Today also we give time to think on the Children. They are our future. They are the seeds of tomorrow. Is there truly anything more precious we have to protect in this world? Think today on our children. Wether you are a mother or father. Wether you are an aunt or uncle. Or perhaps those roles are not yet yours, then remember, that as Thor protects us as children of Midgard, it is our sacred duty to protect our children. To nurture them, to teach them. To lead by example. They are always watching and the example you set could be pivitol in the shaping of who they are becoming. So today also think on your place in the lives of our children. How best can you serve as their protectors, nurturers and role models? This day we also must take in to consideration Fidelity. This is the adherence to responsibilities and loyalty. Thought of most often in our romantic relationships as remaining tru to our partners. But fidelity is more than just a romantic notion. It is the strict observence of promises. Of duty. When you give your word, hold that promise high. People know you by your deads. They will guage their respect and kind regard of you based upon your adherence to what promises you make AND KEEP. Twelfth night is a time of oaths and is approaching fast. Today think on your fidelity, promises you will make to yourself in the new year. And what loyalties you will offer and stand by. Do this in preparation for the night of oaths to come. And do not fear the making of promises. Hold yourself accountable to your word. Strengthen who you are, so that you may be a stronger pillar of your family and your community. Blessings on this seventh night of Yule! Hail Thor! Hail the future and the children of our Folk! Hail those who are loyal, steadfast, and impeccable with their words! By Gythia Melissa Mills Hail Raven Folk United! HAIL OUR MIGHTY GODS!!!! âš¡ ravenfolkunited.org

It is often said we don't know much about her, but I disagree. Although she is not written on extensively, she is written about often enough to allow us to know that this is a most interesting and multifaceted Goddess, Valkyrie and Handmaiden. Blessings to you on this 5th night of yule! This night is sacred to community and hospitality. And how can one have a thriving and solid community without hospitality? I would say that these two go hand in hand. Today, let us think on community. From the small close-knit families and kindreds, to our larger world community honoring the Gods from which we come. To the larger Euro Folk community out there that may still find themselves adrift and unrooted in who they are. How can we keep the bonds of love and kinship strong betwixt our close-knit Folk? The havamal says: The generous and brave live best. Rarely are they burdened by worry and doubt; while the coward lives in fear and the miser mourns when he receives a gift. -HÃ¡vamÃ¡l: Stanza 48 I advise you, Loddfafnir, to take advice; you would benefit, if you took it, good will come to you, if you accept it: do not scorn a guest nor drive him away from your gates; treat the homeless well. -HÃ¡vamÃ¡l: Stanza 135 Friends should exchange weapons and gifts for it is obvious that friendships last longest between those who understand reciprocity -HÃ¡vamÃ¡l: Stanza 41 Our relationships that are built on reciprocity, kindness and generosity rarely see a negative return. Years ago I opened my home to my folk. Many miles lay between us. We are spread out and it can create some difficulties when building a community. So I invite them to come and stay the night or the weekend. To share lunch and supper and breakfast together. To sit and share longer conversations to have the opportunity to really get to know each other in a way that a get together at a resteraunt or a couple hours in a park can not provide. These weekend house parties spent together and sharing ritual honoring our Gods and ancestors are what were instramental in building the community we have here in my state, as well as the larger community from further afar. Hospitality became a signature of my Kindred. As we have taken it seriously to invite our Folk in and make known to them that they are welcome, cared for, and part of us. What acts of hospitality do you offer now? What acts of hospitality can you offer in the year to come? And what community, what bonds of frith and ties of friendship shall you build? We must gather to us all of kin. We must find ways to unify our Euro Folk. I encourage you to take the words of Odin in the Havamal and make use of the time honored tradition of hospitality. Celebrate the community you have, and think on its continued growth and strength. By Gythia Melissa Mills, Hail the High One! Hail the Generous Hosts! Hail the Folk! âš¡ ravenfolkunited.org

Wishing you a blessed 4th day of Yule! On this day we honor Aegir, Freyr, and Njord. Aegir was known for his great hospitality. Always hosting the Gods gladly and making sure they were well provided for. In all things except, the Mead which wld inevitably run out. One of the most well known stories in our Lore is that of Tyr and Thor Traveling to procure a cauldron large enough for Aegir that he would be able to brew enough Mead to host the Gods without being short of Mead. Think upon the hospital nature of Aegir today. Do you embody this in relation to your people? Hospitality is a virtue. It's how we show care and respect for those in our lives. In this Yule season do not allow the world to make you feel so busy in the holiday rush that you forget this virtue. Be a gracious host. Spend time with those you love and care for and treat them to the best you have to offer. There will be reciprocity in the giving of hospitality. One of the greatest gifts of the season. Helping build those bonds of kinship. So set a cup of Mead for Aegir this night and thank him for his example in being the most gracious of hosts. Njord is known for his connection to prosperity. Multiplying wealth. On this day perhaps set your intentions of what it is you wld wish to grow your prosperity in. Write down your goal in this. Light a candle for Njord, and/or give Blot to him. Take the paper you wrote your intentions of prosperity on and burn it, sending it off in request to Njord. Freyr. Also a God of prosperity but tonight consider his other aspect, as God of the harvest. What did you harvest this year? What rewards did you plant the seeds of and see to fruition this year? The literal harvest of fields for your family and community? The rewards of hard work in your profession? Light a candle or give Blot to Freyr as well and honor what has been reaped. And thank him for the blessings. Ask that he be with you in the new year when you plant these new imtensions and seeds of the future. Take time throughout today also to think on love. What sweetness in life would there be without those we love to share it with? Who but those we love would be there to take our hand in the hard times or to raise a glass with us in celebrating life's achievements? There are many kinds of love, the excitement of a lover in the blushing bud of new and fragile love. Just embarking on the adventure of discovery together. Or in the time tested and True love that has been tempered by the fires of this life and still has the power to heal or encourage with a look or a touch. The love of a child. Dependent on you and looking into your eyes with youthful adoration and trust. The love of a parent or one who has had a hand in guiding you through the perils and triumphs of your life, with an encouraging word or a shoulder to lay your weary head on for a brief respit, when the world has taken a little to much from you. Remember to honor the love you recieve, and your ability to to give it back in equal measure today. Sending you love and wishes of prosperity and peace over what you have reaped this year. By Gythia Melissa Mills Hail Raven Folk United! Hail Aegir! Hail Njord! Hail Freyr! âš¡ ravenfolkunited.org

Wishing you a glad 3rd Day of Yule! This day is sacred to Mani, God of the moon. It is right that at this time we honor him with our longer nights soon growing shorter. A time to thank him for that brief respite of long days toiling in the sun. And again for the long nights with the shining stars and glowing moon that can be navigation for traveling and inspiring us to move in our own lives through the mysterious power of their celestial beauty. Now on this 3rd day of Yule we also focus on courage. It takes courage to walk through the darkness. The darkness of night, and the darkness that sometimes visits our lives. It takes courage to know that we shall walk out again into the sun shinning upon our faces. That we shall again plant seeds that take root and grow. Both in the fields we plow to sustain us and our people. And the seeds of change and new beginings we plant to grow rooted in our hearts and directed by our dreams of the future. Know that when the light seems to have left you, you are never alone. Take heart, your people stand beside you. Your ancestors encourage from over your your shoulder. And the Gods will point the way if you only take the time to be still, and listen. Hail Mani! And Hail the courageous! By Gythia Melisa Mills

"'Night' men call it, 'Darkness' gods name it, 'The Hood' the holy ones high; The giants 'The Lightless,' the elves 'Sleep's joy' The dwarfs 'The Weaver of Dreams.'" (Alvissmal) Mother's Night is actually a celebration to the Mother of Night, the goddess Nott herself; for she brings forth the dawn and births dagr. On this Night we remember the first fimbul winter when the sun was not seen, when the hearts of men and gods alike sought a new day to come. We gather with family, to be joyful for all we had and to pray for protection in the darkness from the ills of the cold and weary Night. We offer libation. for a gift for a gift is our way. Together we alight a flame anew in our home as ward to keep us warm and offer us light while we await days thrice for the dawn to come. Soon, shall odin ride the wild hunt, prepare we offerings to hang on our sacred tree, a gift for a gift we give. Gothi James A.- Of the PNWWP

A New year aproches Vices and basic impulses are like the teeth of fenrir, and it is our daily duty to fight the wolf. To respect oneself, is to moderate one's basic impulses in perspective of higher purpose and or personal goals. We can not claim to be a people of higher principles yet continuously chase pleasure and flee from pain at a whim like simple lab mice. We must individually strive for more so that collectively we can become more! This realm can be hard and filled with much pain and suffering yet I believe It is our duty to endure the forge in order to reach past the Veil of normality. Complacency and excuses have led us as a people to the literal verge of extinction, there is no more pressing purpose in our lifetime than to secure a future for the generations that proceed us. The individual and their discipline or lack thereof will ultimately determine the outcome of this cosmic struggle that takes place both on the macrocosm and microcosm simultaneously. As deeds are our worth, and this is constantly reinstated in our lore, I urge our folk to be more or be forgotten! We must remember that the wolf doesn't eat the unlucky deer, it eats the weak one and that we must earn our right to exist in nature. START TODAY!! Be strong and choose discipline over impulse! Choose strength over weakness!! Look to our mighty Gods for inspiration not handouts!!!! Stand up and Hail our Gods with honor and wipe the shame and weaknesses from your brow for you are descendents of Europa!! Michael Sessumes, Hildingr Hail Raven Folk United!! Balance is the universal struggle that seems to be the most prevalent for both the Gods and for man alike. The balance of Order and chaos both within oneself and rippling out-word continuously on the cosmic scale. Creation and destruction, battle and birth both connected in a timeless dance of eternal existence, towards what end we mortals can only ponder in hopes that one day we will truly grasp and finally understand. In man's timeless attempt at eventually fully comprehending his own self and true purpose for existence the world has seen many great minds and warriors so numerous that our own sagas can hardly keep track, yet these combined attributes have proven to be a far more illusive occurrence amongst the pages of history. The men who have ascended from the realm of normality and went on to be remembered for conquests and true Glory the likes the world had never before previously seen were almost always warriors with great minds and a deep spiritual connection to their Gods and the ancestral traditions of their folk. A firm stance on moral ethics and a true understanding of social conduct is what separated and currently separates Nobility from the common warrior even in modern times. OUR PURPOSE IS CLEAR!! To create a Folk Nation for our people under our sacred Raven Banner! To kneel only to our God's and to crush all enemies with no truce! We as Raven Folk hold our woman high as they hold a divine connection to our God's! They are both the life bringers and magic of our mighty Folk! We are no longer the nations that have betrayed our people. Once Germanic Celtic or Slavic we are now Raven Folk! A pan European people directly created from the GODS themselves!!!! Michael Sessumes, Hildingr Hail Raven Folk United!!!! HAIL OUR MIGHTY GODS!!!!

A love for their lineage. Once there take a look around. feel, see, and know who surrounds you. And keep in mind even the worst ancestors have the best intentions. They still have love and maybe even regret, that will be let go. Everything they have done was a step to bring you to who you are. Every success, every mistake, every love that happened. It all made you, you. (Stop reading for a moment and think of your ancestors, who's coming to mind) The ancestors surround you and there are so many. More than you could possibly know. They are filled with happiness and love to share with you their wisdom of what their lifetime taught them. Now envision you gathering with them around a fountain. A fountain with an amber glow that you energetically put your hands in. Instantly you feel the divine energy and see it move through you, through your meridians, cauldrons through your crown. moving through you to your grandparents, and theirs and theirs. It starts to reach and move through both sides of your family's lines. Through all that has passed. Moving back through generations. Through timelines, through dimensions. Moving back and back. moving through each person tied to your bloodline. Moving through and healing each person with this beautiful warm amber glow. As it moves back through time it heals each soul. Which heals through time. Past, present, future. The light is going back so far through so many souls until it reaches a beach. It moves into a branch of a tree, surrounded by three Gods. Odin, Vili, Ve. You feel the power, the divine energy, the healing of the amber and the vril. The life force, the breath, the ond that Odin breaths into you. Now you are not only feeling the healing energy, you are feeling that God energy. Here take a moment and some breaths to take it in. Breathe until you feel the connection until you feel you are no longer a dense human but a Godlike being sharing Odin's energy. You are empowered by it, and remember who you are and what you are capable of.

I feel this meditation is so important so I wrote it in a way that you can hopefully read it slowly as you bring the ancestors to you. I suggest before you start, get comfy, and in a quiet place and plan for a good 15 min. Thank you and enjoy Gythia Heather Clinkonbeard, Hail the Gods and Goddesses! Hail the folk! Hail the Raven Folk United! Hail the ancestors!! This is a guided meditation that you read to yourself. Prepare by grabbing your favorite crystals, candles, tools, and water and sit in a quiet place. Plan to spend about 15-20 min. Clear your space first setting intentions to be protected while you connect with the ancestors. Now that you are in a quiet place and feeling comfortable, start to notice your breath. Take slower breaths that fill your lungs, and your stomach and open you up. Breathing in through your nose, envision the breath moving through your body, noticing anywhere that feels stuck, and push through with the breath and breathe out your mouth. Stop reading for a moment and take several breaths this way, until you feel your mind clear, your body relaxed and you are present in the moment. Breathing in through your nose, and out through your mouth long, deep, breaths. Clearing, cleansing, and grounding. (Stop here for breaths) Now we envision our roots connecting to the ground. Sink your roots deep..... deep into the earth. Feeling the richness and wisdom of all that has come before moving through the soles of your feet. Continue the deep breaths and visualize the earth's energy with each breath in filling up your physical body. Do this until you can see, and feel the energy moving and flowing through your physical body. The earth energy will push through anything that doesn't serve. Any aches and pains, stagnant energy. So again takes a few moments to work with your breath and the earth's energy to feel healed and grounded. (Stop here for grounding to earth) At this point, you feel wonderful, feel present, feel connected, and feel the healing energy moving through your physical body. Take a moment now to call in your guides, your Fylgia, and your ancestors. Set intentions that you will journey to speak with them, to share energy, healing, and wisdom. Call in all that have your highest and best to journey with you today. Envision any runes you use that help guide and protect you. (this is personal for each person and I suggest only using one you are familiar with and used before) Now in your mind's eye, notice way ahead of you an ancient tree. The Yggdrasil tree. So large you can't see around it, above it, or below it. You see and feel how ancient this tree is but also how powerful it is. Energetically you can feel it holds the secrets of time, timelines, and realms of everything. It is a portal to travel to halls, to God's, to Goddesses, to our higher self. Today we are making our way to meet with our ancestors. Once you make your way to the tree take a moment right in front of the tree to feel all it has to offer. To see and feel what it looks like for you. We again set intentions that we will enter this tree knowing we will shed lifetimes of hurt and habits that no longer serve. We are ready to let it all go. We set intentions that we are going to heal, ourselves and all connected to us. Past, present, future. This is where you can ask questions or ask for guidance. (Take a moment to see your intentions) Now the door opens and your guide walks you across to a door on the other side. You are walking over a bridge of sorts, envisioning with each step that you shed more and more and everything that holds you back. Illness, generational habits, addictions, pain, heartache. Not just yours in this life but all that is tied to you by your ancestors. You are feeling lighter and lighter as you make your way to the door on the other side. The door opens and you can feel a familiar feeling of someone who loves you. Many someone's that love you. A love for their kin.

Victories Breath In this modern age of social and technological warfare, syi opps and social manipulation on a global scale our people find ourselves in a unique and troublesome situation that no generations before could have even thought possible. The threat to our very existence on a physical and spiritual level has never been so overwhelmingly prevalent yet we still resist. If we achieve Victories Breath in this eternal struggle we will share a glory unmatched throughout the pages of history but if we fail then all the sorrow and pain that will unfold onto our people will forever be our burden to bear. Our struggle in it's complexity also has a core truth that can not be denied, this truth is the understanding and undeniable fact that if we united and focused we'd be unstoppable yet what it will take for this to actually happen and manifest within a timeframe sustainable for success is something that many of us refuse to doâ€¦â€¦â€¦. Each of us as individuals must look at ourselves honestly in deep reflection and be honest with our own flaws and aggressively fix them without fail or exception. We have allowed ourselves to become weak, we make excuses for our failures and we take every opportunity for self pleasure instead of sacrifice for the greater good. We throw shows and events on the gize of resistance and the future of our folk yet sit idle and drink beer and socialize endlessly with a million ideas all the same yet no evolution in action or personal goals. We've regurgitated the same tactics for multiple generations with less and less success yet we continue and do so ravenously. Our time is often spent joking and indulging to our own demise. The plight of every single individual of our folk has a future that rests on our shoulders. So I call out to my folk!!! Slap the beer cans out of eachothers hands let go of your vices and weakness! Embrace struggle and strengthen your mind and body! Take this struggle seriously and treat it as it is! This is our duty and we have thus far failed generations of children. It's us to blame. But NO MORE! Either raise the standard or step aside for this is the resistance and Raven Folk is the future! We have no time for those to weak to act! Fill our lungs with Victories Breath and LEAD BY EXAMPLE or get out of my way! Stand with our Folk Nation and Except nothing but victory under the Raven banner! Michael Sessumes, Hildingr Hail Raven Folk United! HAIL OUR MIGHTY GODS!!!!!

As the veil thins be mindful of those around you that you may not see. Set a plate for them at the table, tell your favorite stories, and acknowledge those that have come before you. Take some time to reflect on all it took throughout all of time to bring you to this very moment of you. Reflect on how that will carry on in your children and family. Think of the stories that will be told about you. Reflect on how you can create stories that will echo through time when you are an ancestor. We did an ancestor meditation this past weekend and I will be doing another one late Halloween eve. It was a beautiful meditation that walked us through an ancient tree that helped us shed anything holding us back. Until we reached the other side greeted by our ancestors. We spent time with them and worked with a healing amber that made its way through everyone of our ancestors. Creating amber life lines mimicking the placenta, gathering all the wisdom from each ancestor, from their successes and their failures, from their love and strength. The amber healed as it gathered and brought us to an amazing connection throughout our entire existence. We are at a time that we must evolve. What I just described is one step in doing so and a perfect step to start with, if you haven't. We are being nudged by our God's and given everything we need to become like them, to share in their energy. Everything in this life is an opportunity. An opportunity to heal, to learn, or to grow. We are at a very intense time in life. One of the most intense most of us will ever go through collectively. This veil that's thinning is bringing more than just our ancestors. It's bringing an evil that wishes to destroy us. It is our responsibility to heal, to connect, and to walk this path with more than just words. It is our responsibility to lead by example and stand strong. Bring back the strength in our folk. If you are feeling like your being attacked or you're not able stand on your own, reach out and we together will stand strong. With our ancestors and our God's standing with us. We are a united folk and no longer need to feel alone. Gythia, Heather Clinkonbeard, Tru Folk and Raven Folk United

Kindreds of our Folk! The reality of this life is that with all of its complexities some basic principles will always remain quite simple. What will proceed us into future generations will always be what we as individuals allow to persist. Our duty in the most literal sense is to personally take our people's future into our own hands. Our actions or lack thereof will directly affect everything. Ownership of one's own deeds, follow through and discipline are the fundamental characteristics of our Folk that need to be cultivated in order for us to truly carve out the future we seek. Rest assured no one is coming to save us and any success rests entirely on our shoulders, so smile kinsman! That only means there is great glory to be had! The Raven Folk are a united band of kindreds and individuals. As Hildingr of Raven Folk United I have created a council for each kindred to have a representative on the kindred council that can voice their collective opinions and help upper leadership make policies that directly represent the needs of our Folk. Just as our ancestral tribes before us, we will meet at our Althing each year to hold rituals, tribunal and above all else honor our God's! We aim to resurrect our true ancestral folkways while moving forward as a single folk nation into a very real and modern future. We celebrate the uniqueness of each tribe and the manner in which they perform rituals. We will learn and grow together, united as a single people, as it was meant to be. For more information on how your kindred can become an official kindred of Raven Folk United, please email us at Ravenfolkunited@gmail.com or check us out on line at Ravenfolkunited.org Michael Sessumes Hildingr Raven Folk United Ravenfolkunited.org

Raven Folk Laws #1. Raven Folk United is a collective of individuals and kindreds who: adhere to the ancestral spiritual practices and traditions of our ancestors. Our code of ethics is the Aesirian code of nine. And our God's are that of the Aesir! #2. You must be of ethnic European ancestry. We are a unique people and have a strong urge to preserve our traditions and spirituality, in it's native form. We encourage all tribes of the world to do the same . #3. Basic morality, Raven Folk United will have a Zero Tolerance for sexual degeneracy, harm of a woman or children in any aspect, and for miscegenation or infidelity. Substance abuse to excess of any kind, as well as the use of hard drugs all together are band. As they are both a danger to our folk and to the future. #4. Raven Folk United will have a council of chosen representatives from all Oathed kindreds. Individuals must be attached and invested in a Oathed Kindred inorder to serve on the Raven Folk council. We are a people of many tribes, though we will always welcome individuals, we encourage tribalism as we are our ancestors and are restructuring our native and natural state of being. #5. The Raven Folk is a single united people. We are banned together united as our own Nation Folk, while we encourage all kindreds to be free to govern themselves both spiritually and in civil matters as a community, we must all adhere to the Raven Law. #6. In Ritual, we Honor any and all of our ethnic ancestral God's and spirits while never hailing or inviting those of negative or chaos energies into our circle. We aim to build true bonds of reciprocity with our sacred God's, we will always approach Ritual with respect and due Honor that is warranted of our God's! #7. Impartial Ethics: "Perceived rank matters far less to a man who holds the hearts of his men then it does to a man who holds himself above his men, Thus let no man be beyond reproach or acts of violence if his words or deeds are deserving!" No individual or Kindred is beyond reproach for their deeds and accountability, this is not optional for our Folk. At our yearly Althing all unresolved civil matters will face a tribunal. All parties involved have the right to face each other, and agree to the resolution dicided by the council. In extreme cases that are beyond the normal realm of our folk and our morality, if there is proof that supports the claim then no trial will be given and immediate judgment will be made. #8. Unblemished integrity "Alone in the void of the cosmos or within the crowd of a colosseum keep true to your values and never falter in your actions. For you will always know and the Gods will always see. Honor your Oaths and friendships without fail. Always maintaining a strong sense of reciprocity with the Folk and the Gods." #9. Tribal loyalty amongst our Folk requires members of Raven folk united to not be affiliated with or members of: any organizations that spread distention or dishonor to our Folk. We will work with any organizations or kindreds of our Folk that have the same values, and encourage the unity of our tribes but in that belief certain standards must be kept firm.

The Code of Nine 1. The Code is to HONOUR-- Honour yourself with truth and fairness. Your word is your bond; give your word power by adhering to it. Honour your family and friends with reverence and respect. Honour your love and the way, above all else. Honour is the mark of strength and nobility. 2. The Code is to PROTECT -- Protect with savagery your blood and kin. Let no one and nothing violate your love or the way. Let there always be inequity in defense. Always protect thrice as fiercely as one is attacked. Protection is the mark of the warrior spirit. 3. The Code is to FLOURISH -- Prosperity and growth are key to the survival of the way. Such is the mark of intelligence. 4. The Code is KNOWLEDGE -- Knowledge is power. Seek ever to expand the mind. Never stagnate, for knowledge is a gift from the Gods. 5. The Code is to CHANGE -- Adapting and changing are important for growth and survival. That which cannot adapt or change is doomed to perish. Change is the mark of insight. 6. The Code is FAIRNESS -- Pay all debts, pull your own weight, always hear and consider all sides. Treat others with equity and fairness. Expect the same. 7. The Code is BALANCE -- Remember the law of balance; all that which you do or wish, for good or ill, shall return to you one day. Strive for the good. 8. The Code is CONTROL -- Never lose control to anger or be baited by hostility. Never strike a woman unless your very life hangs in the balance. Never violate the weak or innocent. Never tolerate those who do. Control is the mark of a disciplined mind, a sign of the greatest warriors. 9. The Code is CONFLICT -- Those who follow the way must know the art of combat, weapons, and vengeance. War is part of the path. Always be prepared for hostility. It is a destiny woven into the fibers of our people. Keep body, mind, and training up at all times. Have no remorse in the savagery or conflict. Win, prevail, and survive.

Although we have always been very thankful when new people have reached out to us with an interest to join, we don't include just about anyone. Every member we have let into the circle that is our club, is someone we thought was a suitable of the title brother. We're not some superficial political group: we're a fellowship of men with various backgrounds and with different personalities, united by common core traits consisting of healthy values, good intellect and a degree of physical prowess. One must also do something in order to become something. What seems like a paradox is explained by the concept of personal power or hamingja. Goethe is talking about needing to â€œbe somebody of consequenceâ€ in order to do things of great consequence. To become that, we first must undertake many deeds of seemingly little consequence or insignificance. They are neither inconsequential nor insignificant. Many who have taken great leaps and failed would have been well served by taking many, many small ones - greater and greater - before attempting the one that led to their downfall. Many find it easy to feel the fires of transient passion. Few can maintain a steady flame that never dies. This, then, should be our aim. If we succeed, over time, we will inexorably BECOME, and our deeds of consequence will not easily be counted.
